    {
      "id": "d6cf9169_8a58e665",
      "file_path": "models/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/clamp/controlloop/models/messages/dmaap/participant/ParticipantUpdate.java",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 48,
      "message": "Yes, True. This map is contained within previous map. \n\nMap<UUID, ControlLoopElementDefinition> controlLoopElementDefinitionMap, will have a key(UUID) as ControlLoopElementDefinitionID\n\nMap<ToscaConceptIdentifier, Map<UUID, ControlLoopElementDefinition>> participantDefinitionUpdateMap, will have a key(ToscaConceptIdentifier) as ParticipantID and value as the controlLoopElementDefinitionMap.\n\nThe keys are different for both maps, One will be ControlLoopElementDefinitionID and other as ParticipantID, Yet one contained within the other.\nI have changed the comments for better understanding. Hope it helps.\n\nPlease let me know if i misunderstood your comment.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 7504,
        "name": "Sirisha Manchikanti",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "sirisha.manchikanti@est.tech",
        "username": "Sirisha_Manchikanti"
      },
      "updated": "2021-07-07 14:26:38.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "fc5a76a5_c9c670f9",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "f17b6472_af40820e",
      "file_path": "models/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/clamp/controlloop/models/messages/dmaap/participant/ParticipantUpdate.java",
      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 80,
      "message": "mapMap in PfUtils.java is doing a copy of the map, when i used UnaryOperator.identity()\n\npublic static <K, T, R> Map<K, R> mapMap(Map<K, T> source, Function<T, R> mapFunc,\n            Map<K, R> defaultValue) {\n        if (source == null) {\n            return defaultValue;\n        }\n\n        Map<K, R> map = new LinkedHashMap<>();\n        for (Entry<K, T> ent : source.entrySet()) {\n            map.put(ent.getKey(), mapFunc.apply(ent.getValue()));\n        }\n\n        return map;\n    }\n\nIn a testcase testCopyConstructor in ParticipantUpdateTest, I am able to see that the maps are copied correctly with the usage of UnaryOperator.identity()\nParticipantUpdate other = new ParticipantUpdate(orig);\n\nAm i missing something here? I am using UnaryOperator for the first time.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 7504,
        "name": "Sirisha Manchikanti",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "sirisha.manchikanti@est.tech",
        "username": "Sirisha_Manchikanti"
      },
      "updated": "2021-07-07 14:26:38.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "e9c710ef_ba397a03",
      "unresolved": true
    },
